Class Ride

  • java.lang.Object
    • myVelibRides.Ride
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observer

    public class Ride
extends java.lang.Object
implements Observer
    This class describes a ride between two stations of the myvelib network

    Pasteau Jebbari

      • Ride

        public Ride(PlanningRide planningRide,
            GPSCoordinates departurePosition,
            GPSCoordinates arrivalPosition,
            User user,
            java.lang.Class<?> bicycleType)
        This constructor builds a ride that has to be planned and adds this ride to all the stations' list of observers
        Parameters:
        planningRide - : object that instantiates a class that implement PlanningRide which has to get the departure and arrival stations
        departurePosition - : position from where the user wants to leave (not necessarily a station)
        arrivalPosition - : position where the user wants to arrive (not necessarily a station)
        user - : the user who does the ride
        bicycle - : the bicycle used during that ride

      • newArrival

        public Station newArrival()
                   throws WrongRideException
        This method sets as new arrivalStation of a ride the closest station to the previous arrivalStation, if this previous arrivalStation exists. It also returns the new arrival station. If the previous arrival station doesn't exist, the method throws an exception.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        WrongRideException
